article.headline: Lehigh 62, Navy 60 (OT)
article.story: UPPER MARLBORO, Md. (AP) -- Austen Rowland hit a 3-point basket with 20 seconds to play in overtime Saturday to lift top-seeded Lehigh to a 62-60 win over last-place Navy in the first round of the Patriot League tournament. The Mountain Hawks (18-10) overcame a seven-point halftime deficit and four-point margin in overtime and avoided the first-ever first-round loss by a top-seeded team in the tournament's 14-year history. In the tournament's semifinals Sunday, Lehigh will face Bucknell, who beat Holy Cross 66-60. Navy (5-23) led by 59-55 with 2:06 left in overtime, but couldn't hold the lead -- turning the ball over four times in the final two minutes and making just 5-of-11 free throws in the extra period. The Mids made just 13-of-28 free throws for the game. Navy had a chance to win the game in regulation when Jeff Charles made the first of two free throws to tie the game with 3.2 seconds left, but missed the second. Jason Mgerboff led Lehigh with 19 points and Rowland finished with 17 points. Laramie Mergerson led the Mids with 22 points and 10 rebounds, and Chika Onyekanne added nine points and 11 rebounds. It was Navy head coach Don DeVoe's final game as the Mids' coach. DeVoe's 12-year record at Navy was 184-161.
